cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with text mining and natural language processing. The use of machine learning models such as Support Vector Machines, Convolutional Neural Networks, and Recurrent Neural Networks also suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the task of automatically detecting chemical-protein relations in biomedical literature could also fall under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
